The paper discusses a novel SLAM platform that provides evaluation functionality and toolkit for researchers to develop their own SLAM systems. SLAM is a robotics-related topic, which falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions visualization and applications, which are related to Computer Vision (cs.CV). The platform's ability to handle interactions with input dataset and SLAM implementation suggests a focus on Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the platform's potential for practical usage in SLAM applications indicates a connection to Systems and Control (cs.SY).
